rms form key tenets of the work of Mistra Urban Futures (MUF), an international research centre on sustainable urbanisation based in Gothenburg, Sweden, and working through transdisciplinary research platforms there, in Greater Manchester (UK), Cape Town (South Africa) and Kisumu (Kenya). Additional platforms are being established in southern Sweden, Asia and Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable urban development. 0aUrbanisme durable. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aDávila, Julio D, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Henrietta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParnell, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimon, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWaters, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831111964350 cprintz978144733284840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447332855zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447332855/original  a978-3-11-119643-5 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA